         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/1/60 ¶ Dear Dr M'Adam ¶  ¶ Will you kindly issue an order for fifty copies of the IV, vol of the transactions to be delivered to me by Mr Detmoldt, ¶  as I have a capital opportunity of distributing...</supplied>
            </head>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.01.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Macadam</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 11663 Royal Society of Victoria records, box 2/2, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/1/60</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr M'Adam</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you kindly issue an order for fifty copies of the IV, vol of the transactions to be delivered to me by Mr Detmoldt,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Philosopical Institute of Victoria</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, vol. 4 (1860). The volume could not have been ready by 6 January 1860 since it contains details of, and papers read at, the meetings of 9 and 23 January 1860; it was eventually issued in June 1860 (see M to J. Milligan, 19 June 1860). </seg>
                     <seg style="">William Detmold was the Institute’s bookbinder.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> as I have a capital opportunity of distributing them in Europe &amp; America, if I can get them <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">before Friday evening</hi>
               </seg>. I was too busy to be able to attend the meeting to day.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">yours very regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The byefollowing volumes arrived to night in my seed box from Hamburgh. Pray let the donation at once be entered in the next programme<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>At the Society’s meeting on 9 January 1860, the donations recorded included Parts 1-12, <seg style="color: #000000; ">January-December 1858, of </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Zeitschrift für die </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">gesammten</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Naturwissenschaften</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, from the editors (G. Giebel and W. Heintz)</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold; ">; </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">the first and second parts for 1858 of the G</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">ö</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">ttingen publication </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Bibliotheca historico-naturalis physico-chemico et <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mathematica</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, from the publishers (Vandenhoeck &amp; Ruprecht); and Nos. 9 and 10 of M’s </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta phytographiae australiae</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, from the author. </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">See </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Philosophical Institute of Victoria</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, vol. 4 (1860), p.</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">xxxiv</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> also my fragmenta No 10.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B59.12.02.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
